The recall, announced on Wednesday, involves 2354 Lancer 1.6 litre and Evo derivatives sold between 2003 and 2007.The manufacturer joins Toyota SA, Honda SA, Nissan SA and Mazda SA in recalling more than 270000 cars (made between 2001 and 2014) fitted with airbags made by Japanese supplier Takata.The defective airbags can explode on impact, sending shrapnel into the bodies of drivers and passengers. They have already led to the deaths of eight people abroad, and more than 100 injuries.